text: it was december 2005 and i happened to
be at a customer's holiday party she
came up to me her name was Ellen and
asked me if I'd like to meet her son and
go on a date I was used to my dad
setting me up and he was absolutely
terrible at it so had my mom not been
involved there's a good chance I might
not have met Cheryl and our first date
was Penang on the upper east side and
we're strictly just to meet face-to-face
at last it may be about an hour to an
hour and a half and he called me the
next day he actually text messaged me it
was the first text message I ever
received he asked me out again just
seemed like a fun guy I wasn't looking
for anything I was just got out of a
relationship and I really didn't want to
get serious with anyone it was a real
sort of natural progression and
eventually you just kind of wasn't like
a light bulb you just kind of realize
how you're falling in love with someone
about a year after we met she came away
with the family to rather far away it

September and Bob asked me to go on the

all your parents asking for me to go and
he said I'm the one asking but they've
been wanting you to go for many months
now I think that that's where it clicked
for both of us was the beginning of
January he asked me to move in she moved
in with the intent on and I think Cheryl
said it best I think she said I'm moving

and or when I do move out we're moving

we were in California because I was

frustrated with me and Bob was very
nervous and fidgety at that point I

and everything then she didn't actually
take me seriously when I think about a
cheat she was like yeah of course we'll

like now like I have a ring I can show

it could not have been in less romantic

I closed my eyes and I can't imagine my
